snippet.textDisplay: Just a few days before all of this quarantining began a few of us mothers and grandmothers were commenting on FB about the EXTREMELY irritating school absentee policies that have been in place countrywide for DECADES. Children and parents are shamed and harassed if the students stay home when they are sick more than a few days a year. While students who never stayed home for any reason were crowned with special awards. My children, now grown with kids of their own, felt unbelievable pressure to go to school even if they were ready to pass out. I'm told this policy is due to our "omniscient" government running our education system and particularly limiting funding according to attendance statistics. Dealing with absent students also takes extra time and effort to help them keep up with their school work. But the teachers' union has progressively fought for regulations that encourage teachers to become time clock punchers instead of being the professionals they are. Well, now schools are shutting down because of federal mandates. Schools obey with the claim that their students' health is always their first and foremost concern...! I wonder if the government's Dept. of Education will be brought to it's senses and regulate differently when this is over.

snippet.textDisplay:
What you are doing is great. And I am amongst the silent majority that thinks that way.

I just have a little "negative" (I don't know how to say) comment : Be more openly political.
Why am I saying that? Because first : everything is political. A lot of things you said in this video, or how you said them, displayed some kind of political opinion.

So, be more politically conscious of what you say.

Around the 7 minute mark, you talk about changing social norms, and the example you gave was "So that people stop thinking it's okay to go to work when they are sick"

But people do not choose to go to work when sick, they just don't have the choice. Because if they don't go to work, they don't get paid. And often, when they take sick days, they are frowned upon, or even fired.


So be more consciously political, because you ARE displaying political opinions even when you chose not to "be political|"



And a wise woman once said " Politics is everywhere. Trying to remove politics from something only help the oppressor."

I am not asking you to only now raise awareness on the victims of capitalism on your channel, not at all. But I am merely asking for you to be careful of the little things that we often think do not matter.

Same as that grain of powder on the hands, that we think will not cause much, taking care of retaking political control of the way we express ourselves is surprisingly effective.
